title: Federica Mogherini - Wikipedia
snippet: Federica Mogherini (Italian: [fedeˈriːka moɡeˈriːni]; born 16 June 1973) is an Italian politician who served as High Representative of the Union for Foreign Affairs and Security Policy and Vice-President of the European Commission from 2014 to 2019. title: Federica Mogherini, EU High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Security Policy and Vice President of the European Commission | EEAS
snippet: Federica Mogherini succeeds Catherine Ashton as the European Union's High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Security Policy and Vice President of the European Commission on 1 November. She is also head of the European External Action Service.
